## 5. Application Overview

### Home Dashboard Explanation

When you launch Shamal Tools, you'll see the main dashboard with three tool cards:

1. **Smart Geotagging Tool** - Add or view GPS information in your images
2. **Flight Renaming Tool** - Organize your images with structured names
3. **Map Organizer Tool** - View and organize images on a map

### Navigation Between Modules

- Click any tool card to open that tool
- Use the back arrow (←) in the top-left corner to return to the dashboard
- You can have multiple tools open at the same time

### Common Buttons and Actions

Throughout the application, you'll see these common buttons:
- **Select Folder** - Choose a folder containing your images
- **Scan/Load** - Process the images in your selected folder
- **Export** - Save your work to a new location
- **Preview** - See what changes will be made before applying them

### Status Messages and Progress Indicators

The application shows real-time feedback:
- Progress bars show how much work has been completed
- Status messages explain what the application is doing
- Statistics display counts of processed images

