## 7. Module 2: Flight Renaming Tool

### Purpose of the Tool

The Flight Renaming Tool helps you:
- Give your images organized, professional names
- Track which flight each image belongs to
- Easily sort and find images later

### Naming Format: Flight_XX_XXXX

The standard naming format is:
`Flight_[Flight Number]_[Image Number].extension`

Example: `Flight_01_0001.jpg`

### Step-by-Step Usage

#### 1. Selecting Folder

1. Open the Flight Renaming Tool
2. Click "Select Folder"
3. Choose the folder with images to rename

#### 2. Entering Flight Number

1. Enter the flight number in the "Flight Number" field
2. The first image will start with this number
3. Subsequent images will increment automatically

#### 3. Previewing Rename Results

1. Click the "Preview" button
2. Review the table showing:
   - Original filename
   - New filename
   - Flight number
   - Image number

#### 4. Executing Batch Rename

1. Review the preview carefully
2. Click "Apply Rename" to make changes permanent
3. A confirmation message will appear when complete

### Important Warnings (Overwrite Prevention)

⚠️ **Important Safety Notes:**
- The application creates backup information before renaming
- Use the "Undo Last" button if you need to reverse changes
- Always preview before applying changes
- Original files remain untouched in their original location

### Example Before & After Filenames

| Before | After |
|--------|-------|
| DJI_0001.JPG | Flight_01_0001.jpg |
| IMG_20230515_143022.jpg | Flight_01_0002.jpg |
| PICT0003.BMP | Flight_01_0003.bmp |

