## 8. Module 3: Map Organizer Tool

### Purpose of the Tool

The Map Organizer Tool helps you:
- See where each image was captured on a real map
- Select groups of images by drawing shapes on the map
- Automatically organize selected images into folders
- Export organized images for easy sharing

### How Images Are Placed on the Map

1. The application reads GPS data from your images
2. Each image appears as a marker at its capture location
3. Images without GPS won't appear on the map
4. Zoom in/out to see different areas

### Step-by-Step Usage

#### 1. Importing Images

1. Open the Map Organizer Tool
2. Click "Select Image Folder"
3. Choose the folder containing geotagged images
4. Click "Load Images" to place them on the map

#### 2. Viewing Locations on Map

1. After loading, markers appear on the map
2. Each marker represents one image
3. Zoom and pan to explore different areas
4. Click markers to see image details

#### 3. Selecting Regions or Areas

1. Use the drawing tools on the left side:
   - Rectangle tool: Draw boxes around images
   - Polygon tool: Draw custom shapes
   - Circle tool: Draw circular selections
2. Draw around the images you want to select
3. Selected images will be highlighted

#### 4. Auto-Organizing Images into Folders

1. After selecting images, click "Export Selected Images"
2. Choose where to save the organized folder
3. The application creates:
   - A new folder with your chosen name
   - Subfolders for each selection
   - Copies of selected images in appropriate folders

#### 5. Exporting Organized Data

1. During export, you can:
   - Keep original filenames
   - Rename files during export
   - Add descriptive folder names
2. The exported folder structure makes sharing easy

### Offline Behavior Explanation

- Maps work offline using pre-loaded map data
- Internet is not required for basic mapping functions
- Some advanced map features may require internet connection

